{
  "texts": [
    "We used the EM_aligner solver 8 that was used for the v14 reconstruction and later the Python implementation BigFeta (BigFEa-Ture Aligner (BigFeta): https://github.com/AllenInstitute/BigFeta).",
    "For montages where these solvers did not produce satisfying results, we used the iterative TrakEM2 solver 9 (TrakEM2 solver client: https://bit.",
    "ly/3gCuu98) that enables rigid regularization of per-tile affine transformations but is significantly slower.",
    "This was primarily necessary for the 295 sections that contained images from multiple acquisitions.",
    "We separated the disconnected islands in all 7,050 sections resulting in 48,121 sub-sections."
  ]
}